We recommended that Management:

Encourage the LDRRMO to exert more effort in implementing actions and measures pertaining to all aspects of disaster risk reduction and management towards building a disaster-resilient LGU and communities;

Closely monitor the implementation of all PPAs under the LDRRMF to facilitate corrective action, if any, and the timely reprogramming and reallocation of the fund for its optimum utilization;

See to it that all charges in the LDRRMF are related to four thematic areas of disaster risk reduction and management as prescribed in NDRRMC, DBM and DILG JMC No. 2013-1; and

Require the Municipal DRRM Officer to prepare and submit the monthly Report on the Sources and Utilization of LDRRMF on time and facilitate monitoring of the accomplishment vis-à-vis the targeted projects for effective and efficient utilization of the fund.

We reiterated our prior year’s recommendations that Management strictly comply with DBM and DILG JMC No. 2011-1, as follows: 

Maximize the utilization of the 20 per cent Development Fund and implement the PPAs within the targeted timeframe to achieve the social, economic and environmental outcomes essential in the attainment of the constitutional objective of a desired quality of life for all; 
Reprogram and reallocate resources as soon as the need arises to ensure that the Municipality is maximizing its available resources to achieve the expected results it has committed;

We recommended that: 

Refund of ₱1,923,294.86 representing CY 2012 expenditures that were charged against CY 2013 appropriations be made; 

Reconciliation of the discrepancies noted in recording the prior year’s expenses and the necessary adjustments be made by the OIC-Municipal Accountant; 

Close coordination between the Municipal Budget Officer and the OIC-Municipal Accountant to ensure that all liabilities are taken up in the books at year-end; 

In the future, prior year’s expenses not recognized as payables during the year these were incurred be disallowed for payment by the OIC-Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer; and 

Review on the correctness of the entries made in the Journal Entry Voucher (JEV), journals and ledgers be done by the OIC-Municipal Accountant to ensure an accurate reporting.
